The Kandarin headgear 1 is a reward from completing the easy Kandarin Diary tasks given by The 'Wedge' outside of Camelot castle, and can be retrieved from him for free if lost. Its stats are identical to an iron med helm.

 Attack bonuses
+0+0+0-3-1
 Defence bonuses
+4+5+3-1+4
 Other bonusesSlot
+0+0+0%+0List

Benefits[edit | edit source]

When worn:

  • Extra logs when cutting normal trees anywhere (no additional experience)

When worn or in inventory:

  • Functions as a light source

Always, even when not in inventory:

  • The Flax keeper will exchange 30 noted flax daily for 30 noted bow strings
  • Coal trucks hold 140 coal
  • 5% more marks of grace on Seers' Village Rooftop Course

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
24 March 2016
(update | poll)
  • It is now also possible to get multiple copies of achievement diary equipment by talking to relevant diary masters or by talking to Perdu, found upstairs in the Edgeville general store. Perdu will charge a small fee.
  • The "Destroy" option was replaced with a "Drop" option.
15 October 2015
(update)

The "Teleport" option was removed.

16 April 2015
(update)

The 'Wedge' now refers to Kandarin headgears as headgear rather than headband.
